The paper deals with algorithms for exhaustive search on propositional knowledge bases, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the generation of propositional languages, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO). The use of circuits and combinational logic suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of search algorithms, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
